citeinfo.title: Street Segment Simplified SHP - National Geospatial Data Asset (NGDA)

descript.abstract: A vector line file of public/private streets compiled from orthoimagery and other sources that is attributed with street names, addresses, route numbers, routing attributes, and includes a related table of alternate/alias street names. If the purpose of using NYS Streets is for geocoding, the New York State Office of Information Technology Services (NYS ITS) has a publicly available geocoding service which includes the NYS Streets along with other layers. For more information about the geocoding service, please visit http://gis.ny.gov/gisdata/inventories/details.cfm?DSID=1278.
descript.purpose: A vector street layer suitable for use in a GIS.

procstep.procdesc:
From 2001 through 2005, the NYS GIS Program Office (GPO), then part of the NYS Office for Technology (OFT), partnered with the NYS Department of Transportation (DOT) and the NYS Department of Motor Vehicles (DMV), to create a statewide GIS street centerline file for use as the GIS streets database in DMV’s modernized Accident Location Information System (ALIS). The statewide GIS street centerline file was built from the best available local and state sources and was supplemented with contractor sources. The data was subsequently maintained through contracts with Tele Atlas® (now TomTom) until March 2008 and then with NAVTEQ® (now HERE North America LLC) from January 2009 through December 2013. During this maintenance time, the GPO, DOT, and several counties provided updates through the use of an online change notification system. In 2014, the GPO took over all maintenance of the data. Counties and the DOT continually provide updates through the GPO’s online data editing application or directly to the GPO through other communication methods. The GPO continually evaluates edits made to the NYS Address Points data and applies relevant changes to the NYS Streets data to keep the two GIS files in sync.
For this simplified version the file was dissolved on the following fields for improved labeling and increased drawing speeds.
SHIELD HighwayNumber JURISDICTION LeftCountyName RightCountyName LeftCityTownName RightCityTownName Label
All other Fields have been removed.
